Taiwan Stocks: Motech Industries, Nanya Technology, Neo Solar

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-06-17T06:00:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/au-formosa-petrochemical-young-fast-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 18.33, or 0.2 percent, to 8,636.10,
the lowest close since March 29. The stock fell 2.3 percent this
week.  Solar energy-related companies:  Motech Industries Inc. (6244) 
(6244 TT), a solar-cell maker, increased 0.5 percent to
NT$102.50, the highest close since June 1.  Neo Solar Power Corp. (3576) 
(3576 TT) rose 2 percent to NT$55.  Sino-American Silicon
Products Inc. (5483)  (5483 TT) climbed 1.8 percent to NT$90.10.  Polysilicon, the main raw material in solar panels, has
plunged more than 33 percent in the  spot market  during the
second quarter, according to data compiled by Barclays Capital
and Bloomberg.  Nanya Technology Corp. (2408)  (2408 TT) slumped 7 percent to a
record NT$9.35.  Inotera Memories Inc. (3474)  (3474 TT) slid 6.7 percent
to NT$9.98, the lowest close since January 2009. The nine-day
decline is the longest losing streak since October 2008.
 Powerchip Technology Corp. (5346)  (5346 TT)  dropped 3.9 percent to
NT$4, the lowest close since July 2009. The price of DDR3 2-
gigabit dynamic random-access memory fell 0.6 percent today, a
third day of losses, according to data by TrendForce Corp.â€™s
